I enabled the new Labs Feature "Kanban Backlog". As soon as I enabled it and mapped the status "Backlog" to the boards pseudo-column "Backlog" issues for some users are displayed spanning all columns (Attachment "Span-Without-Filter").

I found a workaround that involved creating a custom quick filter (Attachment "Quick-Filter") explicitly hiding issues with status "Backlog". Applying the quick filter to the board, the issues now display correctly (Attachment "No-Span-With-Filter") but it would be nice to know why it happened in the first place.

We deployed with success JIRA 7.0.10 (upgraded from Jira 6.4.9)
But issue navigator does not return any result.

In log file, there is the following exception
